section.div: This project focuses on developing a system to detect and mitigate Distributed Denial of Service (DDoS) attacks using the Random Forest machine learning algorithm. By analyzing network traffic patterns, the system can identify potential DDoS attacks in real-time and implement preventive measures, ensuring network security and reduced downtime.
Automated Selenium-based scraper for PimEyes, enabling reverse face search for Open-Source Intelligence (OSINT) applications. Streamlined data extraction for enhanced investigative capabilities.
A openCV program that detects faces and displays Tiktok cats.
Code samples for my book "Neural Networks and Deep Learning"
